pullRequest.body:
Compared to extras, extensions currently don't allow bypassing the `__fix_json` function, which results in extras being able to export values with empty objects, but extensions can not.


Here is an example of the same data exported through extras and extensions. Note how the extension data is empty. This is because keys with empty dicts are filtered out.

```json
"nodes":[
    {
        "extensions":{
            "EXT_my_extension":{
                "components":[
                    {}
                ]
            }
        },
        "extras":{
            "components":[
                {
                    "test_components::Marker":{}
                }
            ]
        },
        "mesh":0,
        "name":"Cube"
    }
],
```

This PR enables export extensions to define which of their glTF extensions should be passed through without using `__fix_json`. The result is that the keys with empty dict values are kept in the same way extras keeps them.

```json
"nodes":[
    {
        "extensions":{
            "EXT_my_extension":{
                "components":[
                    {
                        "test_components::Marker":{}
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        "extras":{
            "components":[
                {
                    "test_components::Marker":{}
                }
            ]
        },
        "mesh":0,
        "name":"Cube"
    }
],
```

This is an example implementation for an export extension which writes a single glTF extension:

```python
def passthrough_extension_data(self, passthrough_extensions, gltf2_plan, export_settings):
    passthrough_extensions.append(glTF_extension_name)
```
---

This fix is essentially the same as was done for extras in https://github.com/KhronosGroup/glTF-Blender-IO/pull/1429

The implementation is a hook because it seems better for backward compatibility to allow extensions to opt-in.

I am currently trying to port some functionality from extras to an extension, and this difference in exporting data is blocking the transition. I can go into my use case more if it's relevant. I'm also happy to make any naming changes to the hook names, etc.

This PR also fixes https://github.com/KhronosGroup/glTF-Blender-IO/issues/870
